    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <head>73. Note From Howe (<gloss target="#t_SS_1">S/S</gloss>) to <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF_1">John Foster Dulles</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d73fn1">Source: Approval of recommendation for
                        a new strategic concept; transmits draft letter to <persName
                            corresp="#p_MNH_1">McElroy</persName> from Dulles. Top Secret
                        Attachments (not included). 1 p. NARA, <gloss target="#t_RG_1">RG</gloss>
                        59, <gloss target="#t_SS_1">S/S</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                        Files: Lot 63 D 351.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1958-07-17">July 17, 1958</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d73-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d73-1"/>
                <p>THE SECRETARY</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Basic National Security Policy (<gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                            >NSC</gloss> 5810/1); <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss> Review of
                        Military Paragraphs 13 and 14 Scheduled on July 24, 1958</hi>
                </p>
                <p>On July 16 you approved recommendations contained in Mr. Gerard Smith’s
                    memorandum of July 15; 1) that you inform the Secretary of Defense that you have
                    concluded that we must now begin to move toward a new strategic concept and 2)
                    that you suggest to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MNH_1">McElroy</persName> that you
                    jointly propose to the President that <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                    consideration of paragraphs 13 and 14 of <gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>
                    5810/1 be deferred until October and State and Defense immediately undertake the
                    joint study of an alternative strategic concept (Tab II).</p>
                <p>Mr. Smith has drafted a letter to Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MNH_1"
                        >McElroy</persName> for your signature along the lines of the
                    recommendations that you approved yesterday (Tab I ).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Fisher Howe</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
